# Optional: public Google Calendar → Upcoming Events section
# In Google Calendar: Settings for the calendar → “Access permissions” → make it public
# → “Integrate calendar” → copy “Public address in iCal format” (ends in .ics)
GOOGLE_CALENDAR_ICAL_URL=https://calendar.google.com/calendar/ical/85e58367b2fbd0f37a51518f2cc9c4fe14ac24eaa31840e0e5691b99416a6e7e%40group.calendar.google.com/public/basic.ics

# Optional: link for “View in Google Calendar” (embed or open in browser)
GOOGLE_CALENDAR_PUBLIC_URL=https://calendar.google.com/calendar/embed?src=85e58367b2fbd0f37a51518f2cc9c4fe14ac24eaa31840e0e5691b99416a6e7e%40group.calendar.google.com&ctz=America%2FNew_York

# Optional: IANA timezone for displaying times (default America/New_York)
# CALENDAR_TIMEZONE=America/New_York

# Optional: Chapter lineage (About section) — Google Sheet as CSV
#
# IMPORTANT: Put these in `.env.local` (create it in the project root). Next.js does
# not load `.env.example` — that file is documentation only.
#
# You may paste either the full sheet URL or only the spreadsheet id:
# GOOGLE_SHEETS_LINEAGE_SPREADSHEET_ID=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/XXXXXXXX/edit?gid=0#gid=0
# …or…
# GOOGLE_SHEETS_LINEAGE_SPREADSHEET_ID=XXXXXXXX
#
# - Row 1: headers — Line Name | Semester/Year | Member 1 | Member 2 | …
#   (An extra “Dean” column is ignored if present.)
# - Each data row: one crossing line; displayed as “Semester/Year: Line Name”.
# - Share the sheet: “General access” → Anyone with the link → Viewer
#   (no Google Cloud project or API key required)
# - Spreadsheet ID = the long id in the URL:
#   https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/<SPREADSHEET_ID>/edit
# GOOGLE_SHEETS_LINEAGE_SPREADSHEET_ID=
# Optional: tab id from URL &gid=… (first tab is usually 0). Omit if you paste a full URL that already includes gid=
# GOOGLE_SHEETS_LINEAGE_GID=0
# Optional: Executive board (Leadership section) — Google Sheet Name | Position
# Same sharing rules as lineage. Optional column "Photo" = path from site root (e.g. /Leadership_Headshots/x.jpg).
# GOOGLE_SHEETS_EXECUTIVE_BOARD_SPREADSHEET_ID=
# GOOGLE_SHEETS_EXECUTIVE_BOARD_GID=0
#
# Optional: cache (seconds) for all Google Sheet CSV fetches in production. Falls back to
# GOOGLE_SHEETS_LINEAGE_REVALIDATE_SECONDS if unset. Dev always uses no-store.
# GOOGLE_SHEETS_REVALIDATE_SECONDS=300